<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Lith Ahntalon on 06-05-2002 11:23 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">/nod Boanerges


It is really quite simple. Most classes can solo and solo effectivly now. The hybrids Ranger/SK/Pallies do quite well now with the combination of spells/gear. Monks are soloing machines. Even warriors with some decent gear can solo well. Sadly, with a gear combination a, no mana, warrior actually has MORE utility than a cleric. They can invis, slow, snare, SoW, shrink, buff STR, etc. Excuse me while I go summon some food/water and hope the mobs eat and drink themselves to death for exp. Warriors midigate damage to such effect that not much healing is needed or they can throw or they can simply regen what little is lost back. Don't get me wrong, I am NOT crying for a nerf of these classes, I am happy for thier freedom but, the time of having a dedicated healer is fading into nothingness barring raids and a few zones. I am a pretty well geared cleric in terms of HP/AC/Mana/FT/spells with 30 AA and quite frankly can solo fairly effectively myself. It is only through a combination of gear/AA/spells/level that I can do this though and my hunting grounds are really restrictive. Maiden's Eye, The Grey and Howling Stones are my only real choices if I wish to solo, the latter two have risks of their own if it comes to CR due to lack of utility. 

The six man group is being replaced by solo or two to three man teams in the name of efficency for exp/AA. Clerics are on the bottom end of that pick of the list because we are so lopsidedly defensive in nature in a game that requires less and less healing for exp. What the answer is, I do not know, the easy answer is more damage output even if restricted to undead. Long term, I cannot say the effects though.

[This message has been edited by Lith Ahntalon (edited 06-06-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
